<br>
1)  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Do not give anyone you don't know anything you do not expect to get back</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Thieves exist, and they thrive off the goodwill of others.  You might describe so-and-so as &quot;nice&quot; or &quot;kind&quot;, but a scammer reads &quot;sucker&quot; and they know that P.T. Barnum was right--there's one born every minute.  If someone just can't wait to see what they'll look like with Soufire or a horse, tell them to use their imagination--or maybe go to EQPixelArmy.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Do all your business transactions through the Bazaar's Trader Mode</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  It's been a while since someone has exploited this, but there's some kind of bug with the trade window and it's not 100% safe.  No one has reported any shenanigans with the Bazaar's Trader mode, and, although that does not prove it's secure, it's known that the trade window was not secure.  Perhaps the bug there has been fixed, but I am not aware if it has.<br>
<br>
Basically, as Fox Mulder of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The X-Files</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> always advocated, trust no one.<br>
<br>
3) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>If the worst should happen, and something is stolen from you, /petition, /report, and e-mail the GMs right away</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  The sooner you contact them, the sooner they can recover your stolen item(s).<br>
<br>
Part of the burden is on you, the potential target of the scam.  Be suspicious of others, especially when it involves big-ticket items like horses or your Priceless Velium Handwraps.  Coming here to report a thief may not prevent her or him from continuing to operate, but if everyone takes some basic precautions, then some scams will be prevented.<br>
<br>
Also, be somewhat wary when buying items.  A very rare few people have been burned by being sold &quot;hot goods&quot;, only to have the GMs take them away and accuse the buyer of being the thief.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Caveat Emptor</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, indeed.<br>
